A **variable** in simple terms is a storage place which has some memory allocated to it. Basically, a variable used to store some form of data.

There are many type of variable
    local-acceess only from the that fuction
    global-access from any fun
    static-A variable that retains its value between multiple function calls is known as static variable. 
    Automatic-All variables in C that are declared inside the block, are automatic variables by default. auto int y=20;//automatic variable
    External-External variable can be shared between multiple C files.We can declare external variable using extern keyword.
 
**Keywords** are specific reserved words in C each of which has a specific feature associated with it 
There are a total of 44 keywords in C 

const: const can be used to declare constant variables.

.c file convert to .s file after compiling 

